description: For sale: $869,900. Built on a private 3.5-acre lot, this exquisite walkout rambler offers the convenience of main level living and an extensive list of desirable upgrades to suit all your wants and needs.  An open layout and vaulted ceilings make the home feel bright and airy, while oversized windows lend beautiful, serene views throughout.  On the main level, you'll enjoy large living spaces that include the vaulted great room with a wall of windows and stone surround fireplace, gourmet kitchen with gorgeous cherry cabinetry and pendant lighting over an impressive 2-tier center island, formal and informal dining, and an incredible addition of a four-season porch surrounded by cedar shakes and a vaulted cedar ceiling, where you can relax next to its floor-to-ceiling stone surround fireplace.  You'll also appreciate having two main level bedrooms with California Closet systems, including the spacious Owner's suite and its updated en suite, as well as other updated conveniences, like the ¾ bath, laundry room, mudroom and walk-in pantry.  In addition, the lower level is perfect for entertaining with its cozy family room, full wet bar, billiard room, office/hobby room, third bedroom and full bath, while the walkout leads to a great paver patio with a natural gas fire pit in the wooded backyard.  Located in a secluded neighborhood, this lovingly cared for home offers peace and tranquility in its park-like setting with abundant wildlife.

description: For sale: $1,195,000. Set on a secluded 2.5-acre lot in the prestigious Wynstone neighborhood, luxurious living awaits you in this custom-built executive rambler.  Masterfully designed and detailed, spacious rooms and astounding amenities enhance everyday living and entertaining- evident the moment you enter through double doors to a grand foyer and breathtaking sightline.  Arched entryways frame serene views through a wall of windows in the great room ahead, while pillars section off the lovely formal dining room with a large bay window, cove lighting and butler's pantry, complete with a sink and fridge.  And through French doors off the foyer, a stately den encased in cherry walls and a coffered ceiling is very private and the perfect place to retreat or spend your work day.  Another coffered ceiling is featured in the great room, along with a double-sided fireplace shared with the hearth room and gourmet kitchen, adorned with white cabinetry, ornate backsplash and gorgeous granite counters.  In addition, a large center island provides extra seating next to the informal dining space that lends access to a vaulted, screened-in porch, perfect for dining and relaxing in in warmer months.  You can also enjoy all of the luxuries of main level living, including two lavish powder rooms and an all-inclusive laundry room with a built-in workstation.  A decorative inlay in the Brazilian cherry hardwood floors then leads you down the hallway to the Owner's suite nestled in its own nook of the home.  This exquisite space features a vaulted tray ceiling and oversized windows overlooking the treed backyard, a massive dressing room with organization system, and sensational en suite that shines with marble on the floors, soaking tub and shower and offers the conveniences of dual vanities, a built-in bench and water closet.  And the walkout lower level is an entertainer's dream with a pub-style wet bar surrounded by rich cherry cabinetry, family room with a brick surround, double-sided gas fireplace shared with a billiards room, and media room with theater seating, not to mention three additional bedrooms and two baths.  Leaving nothing behind in its unique design and upscale features, this dream of a home will make you feel like royalty.

description: For sale: $439,900. Dreaming of life at the lake? A home in the woods? Inside, the upper level features an open floor plan, flooded with natural light and offering gorgeous flooring, white trim, updated bathrooms, a master suite, and a stunning kitchen. In the lower level, you will appreciate the large family room with a wood-burning fireplace, walkout access to the yard, a barnwood feature wall, 2 additional bedrooms & bath. Outside, this home has it all and is perfect for entertaining - surrounded by trees, you'll enjoy the sunken firepit, new large deck, fenced area for chickens or goats and a fantastic detached garage/shop for all the toys! Nothing to do here but move in!

description: For sale: $1,250,000. This large owner designed-built country home with multiple porches is really a way of life.  The perfect destination for family gatherings and celebrations, it features elaborate indoor and outdoor kitchens and an open floor plan that still manages to encourage relaxation with numerous quiet nooks and sitting areas.  The property is only a 5-minute drive from downtown Stillwater, yet private enough to think you live deep in the country with acreage to roam and quick access to public trails. A family friend described it this way:  "This house has a way of making the simplest tasks feel special.  You will love being part of dinner prep. From the sprawling gourmet kitchen to a dinner party outside on the elaborate outdoor kitchen and dining table nestled under draping wisteria vines.  Crackling fires and Sonos speakers add to the ambiance.  Seeing this home standing against a white winter evening is simply breathtaking!  You will find no better place to host family and friends.

For sale: $425,000. Your vision of home starts here on 7.3 acres with breath taking views. Centrally located and only minutes from downtown Stillwater. Why live in the city when you can have country living at its finest with less than a 30-minute drive to St. Paul-Minneapolis. The kitchen is the heart of the home with ample cabinet and counter space for holding all those cookie exchanges. The flow of your casual dining and living room space has more than enough room to host those family get togethers you always dreamed of. Game night, sleep overs, or just pack the house, your family room is fantastic for entertaining not to mention the gorgeous views. Why stop there your new home offers three bedrooms located upstairs with a full bath and a walk-in storage closet to dream of with ample space to make your own. Kick back and relax while you take in all the scenic views as you have your morning coffee and watch the sun come up. This home brings you nothing but pure country joy. You don't want to miss out!

description: For sale: $680,000. Home sits on over 7 acres & is located within Mahtomedi Schools! Schools are a 10 minute drive! A freshly painted hardy plank exterior & new roof create curb appeal. A spacious foyer & 10 foot ceilings throughout the main level create a feeling of grandeur. Handsome beams and a large bay window make a warm home office. The kitchen has maple cabinetry & floors, a large kitchen island w/bar height seating, a built in desk, double ovens & a large pantry. Perfect for entertaining! The great room has a 22ft. ceiling & large windows creating a light drenched open space cozied up by built-in cabinetry & wood finishes. An expansive screened in porch & deck are perfect for enjoying the outdoors. 4 spacious bedrooms on the upper level feature large closets. The owners suite offers double doors, an ensuite full bath & large walk in closet. The lower level has in-floor heat throughout, an amusement area w/ roughed in wet bar & a home theater! Exterior amenities - garden w/spigot & outlet in back!

description: For sale: $699,000. Almost 10 ACRES! Welcome to your secluded sanctuary.  You will love this beautiful home, sitting on just under ten acres at the end of a quiet cul du sac.  The open-concept main floor has gorgeous cherrywood flooring.  Large windows let in plenty of natural light and look out onto your private wooded lot, where you will see all kinds of wildlife.  A large kitchen with stainless steel appliances flows into the spacious great room, with a hand-crafted stone fireplace flanked by built-in bookshelves.  The wood-paneled lower level feels like a cabin getaway, offering an expansive family room, complete with a wet bar and another stone fireplace.  Outside, you and your family can enjoy a professionally landscaped backyard, have a meal on the large deck or stone patio, walk the back trails on your 9+ acres, or enjoy a bonfire on two separate fire pits.  Moreover, you are just minutes from shopping, dining, and fun in beautiful downtown Stillwater. A must see to appreciate the uniqueness!

description: For sale: $639,900. The ideal hobby farm awaits new owners with their sheep, chickens, llamas or horses. Over the last several years, the farm was transformed from a neglected rundown property to an inviting peaceful hobby farm. A renovated & expanded turn of the century farmhouse has been thoroughly updated, creating bathrooms, a charming & functional country kitchen with a huge walk-in pantry. The added space provides all of the functional rooms needed for 21st-century life. A detached garage with a second story for storage could be converted into office or play space. In the center of the farmstead, the solid historic barn stands waiting for its next occupants. Over the last few years, the barn received new doors, was re-roofed, painted (cupola was even painted) and the barn quilt was added. Fencing is in place for sheep, llamas. Chickens have roamed the yard and gardens and had a tight chicken house. The ideal hobby-farm lifestyle awaits!

description: For sale: $459,900. Rare, affordable opportunity to own over 5 picturesque acres minutes from Stillwater with access to the Gateway Trail. Bucolic, rolling hills with pines, hardwoods and gardens surround this solid one-owner home. Seller built the home with 2x6 construction and styrofoam tongue and groove sheathing to make the home very energy efficient. New roof in 2016 with ice and water shield over the entire roof. Views are lovely from every window, even in winter. A little updating will make this home shine. Attached garage has epoxy finish floor along with a floor drain. The large detached shop is 26X36 with room for workshop and room for 2 cars. (Home has been virtually staged in some photos) One year AHS warranty included by seller. New septic system to be installed in spring paid by seller.

For sale: $279,900. Exclusive and prominent North Hill location next to the Stillwater Country Club. This historic 2 story farmhouse sits on a phenomenal picturesque oversized double lot with mature trees and well established garden spaces. The unique floor plan boasts an expansive eat in kitchen with walk in pantry as well as a formal dining space and main floor master which easily could be utilized as an office/flex space. The attached heated garage leads to a generously sized breezeway perfect for added storage and/or entertaining large groups. The home's condition shows years of being well loved and cared for - Quality Andersen Glider windows, low maintenance exterior added storage in garage attic and yard sheds. Notable potential in every square foot.

description: For sale: $825,000. This well maintained executive home has a floor plan that takes in the views of the naturally landscaped acreage on Lake McDonald. Many days are spent enjoying canoeing and fishing right out your back door. Winter months bring cross country skiing and snowshoeing.  The lower level has a wood burning fireplace to warm up in front of after outdoor activities. The large bar area with all new stainless steel appliances (sink, wine fridge and dishwasher) is perfect for entertaining friends and family.

description: For sale: $725,000. Enjoy nature views, wildlife and prairie grasses in this 2.5 acreage setting offering peace and serenity. Dramatic high ceilings, large picture windows allow for beautiful natural light. Main floor bedrooms with a large Owner's Suite, expansive open floor plan, wood floors, enamel cabinets and trim, Andersen windows, office, knockdown ceilings, 2 fireplaces and one see thru, newer stainless steel appliances and double oven, travertine floors and jacuzzi in owner's bath, large walk in closets. The enormous sun room walks out to the backyard oasis offering a pool, paver patios, screened porch and extensive landscaping. The lower level is a full entertainment space with media center, billiard room, full walk behind bar, additional bedroom and 3/4 bath. 2 large storage rooms, over-sized garage, furnace 2015, roof 2017. Quiet cul-de-sac. The best of one level living in the desired Shores of Lake McDonald.

description: For sale: $2,650,000. Incredible custom-built home a picturesque 8.3 acres with a gorgeous swimming pool & beautiful pond views! Superior craftsmanship featuring 10ft-32-ft ceilings, 8-ft doors, built-in surround sound, Acacia hardwood floors & custom woodwork. Gourmet kitchen features granite counters, expansive center island, walk-in pantry & top-of-the-line GE Monogram stainless steel appliances. Great room includes 2-sided gas fireplace with floor-to-ceiling stacked stone, wall of picture windows & 32-ft vaulted ceilings with wood-beam detail. Main level Master Suite boasts a private patio, spa-like luxurious private bathroom with in-floor heat, separate shower & soaking tub, washer/dryer & more!  Upper level includes 4 additional spacious bedrooms, loft area & large laundry room.  Walk out lower level with in-floor heat, theater room, huge wet bar & wine cellar, exercise room, indoor sport court, steam shower, dog bath & so much more! Finished 4-car garage, smart home technology & security system.

description:
For sale: $749,900. Custom built home in Boutwell Farm,  8 other lots to pick from to custom build from the ground up or use one of our existing plans.

Foundation is in and interior of the home is ready to design with our team.  Other lots available to be customized from the ground up!

description: For sale: $1,200,000. Built in 1881 by lumber baron William Sauntry, this majestic home sitting on a hill has been wonderfully restored and upgraded over the years with the most recent work a full kitchen remodel. The home abounds with original Queen Anne Victorian features - intricate inlay floors with several wood varieties, oil on canvas ceilings, beautiful fireplaces, built-in buffet, paneling, light fixtures, and so much more! Enjoy the morning sipping coffee on the wrap around porch or having friends over for wine in the side garden. Five of the bedrooms have en suite bathrooms. The home currently operates as a successful Bed and Breakfast, with the finished attic serving as private owners suite. Sale price is for house and property only; business and furniture sold for an additional amount. If used as a residence, AirBnB revenue could be realized from the main floor suite that features separate entrance.

description: Recently sold: $699,000. Set on a hillside with panoramic views of the St Croix Valley, this captivating walkout rambler is a former Derrick Custom Homes model and offers a desirable open floor plan with all living facilities on the main level.  Enjoy a private master suite with a stunning en suite and huge walk-in closet, office with built-ins and a granite desktop, stone surround fireplace flanked by built-ins in the great room, spacious gourmet kitchen and dining area, laundry room and mudroom with convenient built-in lockers.  The home also boasts coffered, wood-paneled and vaulted ceiling treatments, gorgeous cherry hardwood floors and millwork, and bonus built-in workstations.  The lower level is incredibly designed with another beautiful stone surround fireplace and matching pillars, built-in entertainment center, rustic wet bar and recreation area perfect for entertaining, plus three bedrooms, a full bath and half bath.  The walkout then leads to a paver patio and fire pit in the backyard, in addition to a deck and cozy three-season porch encased in wood paneling with a gas fireplace- all lending those priceless scenic views.  Lovingly maintained and in like-new condition, this home is one to be treasured for years to come.
Recently sold: $340,000.

description: Recently sold: $189,500. Inviting 2 BR 2 BA townhome in prime Stillwater location. This spacious three-level townhome features over 1500 sf and a well-designed, expansive open concept living room with gas fireplace and large windows. You'll love the cozy balcony which is recessed from the building facade creating privacy and protection from the elements. The kitchen features tile floors, subway tile backsplash, gas range and breakfast bar, and opens directly to the living room. The upper level consists of both bedrooms including a spacious master bedroom with walk-in closet and ceiling fan, and full bath. Downtown Stillwater, major retail and shopping, grocery, service businesses all within 10 minute drive. Two State Parks within 30 minute drive. Or hop on your bike and access Brown's Creek State Trail, just 1/2 mile away from the property, and enjoy miles of paved bike trails. Stillwater schools ISD 834.

description: Recently sold: $939,000. Set on a prime 2.5-acre lot surrounded by woods and wetlands in the prestigious Galway neighborhood, this outstanding property offers the convenience of main level living and a practical floor plan that leaves no space unused. Lavish features include custom cherry cabinetry and built-ins, Cambria counters, stylish lighting, three double-sided fireplaces, red birch hardwood flooring and custom wainscoting and coffered ceiling treatments. Main level offers open concept through the dazzling great room and gourmet kitchen, a screened-in porch overlooking the wooded backyard, private master suite with fireplace in sitting room and luxurious bath, 2nd bedroom with en suite bath, stately office, laundry and mud rooms. Walkout lower level great for entertaining with floor-to-ceiling fireplace between family room and 2nd kitchen/wet bar, theater room, exercise room, 2 bedrooms and 2 baths, and backyard is a retreat with a hot tub off the covered patio, large fire pit and impressive sport court.
Recently sold: $430,000.

description: Recently sold: $432,000. Come gather family and friends, all will feel at home! Step inside and you are warmly welcomed by this timeless Craftsman home featuring an elegant staircase accentuated by incredible stained glass windows. Rich woodwork including wainscoting and box beam ceilings, Oak and Maple hardwood floors, built-in hutch. Amazing butler's pantry, cheery kitchen with large windows, center island, granite counters and stainless steel appliances. There are 3 spacious bedrooms upstairs including a lovely master suite with glorious "sleeping porch" that is now year round living space. Large closets throughout, 2nd floor laundry. Fantastic, open and flowing layout.The lower level has a 4th bedroom, full bathroom and great family room. Forced air heat and AC, 2 car garage, newer windows, expansive front screened porch. Truly turn-key, this quintessential home is centrally located on Stillwater's premier Pine Street, just blocks from the Historic Courthouse, bakeries, restaurants and Washington Square Park.

Recently sold: $368,500. Don't miss out on this spacious multi-level home that offers over 4200 square feet. Features a center island kitchen, vaulted ceilings, impressive private multi-level master bedroom retreat, generous finished walkout lower level with large family room and fireplace, additional rec room with endless possibilities, 3 car garage and 2 decks overlooking a very private backyard. New carpet and freshly painted. Great location! Situated on a quiet cul de sac lot in the sought after Oak Glen neighborhood. Close to many walking trails, Brown's Creek/ Gateway Trail system for biking and more.

Recently sold: $350,000. Bright natural lighting upstairs in living, dining, and kitchen space. New laminate wood flooring in main living spaces. 2 bedrooms upstairs, 2 bedrooms downstairs. Split entry. Beautiful in-ground pool with brand new liner, multi-color pool light, and brand new automated retractable cover. Brand new Azek deck. New roof and gutters. Wonderful two-level home with walkout basement to outdoor patio.

Convenient main floor laundry, large rooms great for gatherings and new carpet throughout. Located just minutes from downtown Stillwater, parks, tons of great restaurants & the beautiful St. Croix River. Come take a look!

description: Recently sold: $259,000. Large end unit features stainless appliances, granite island, cherry cabinets, upper level laundry, HUGE master suite w/private bath & walk-in closet. Bright, open floor plan with sunny patio with great views of sunsets & open fields. Mllbrook is a picturesque community located in historic Stillwater, offering many lifestyle amenities including a fishing pier, gazebo, 2 parks, tot-lot & walking trails. Stillwater schools, close to downtown, shops, restaurants and the St. Croix River!

Recently sold: $560,000. Enjoy this custom built waterfront home on an expansive lot in the Legends of Stillwater community.  The home sits on over half-an-acre with the perfect yard for entertaining or to add a future in-ground pool.  Enjoy the lake view and fall leaves from the fire pit or the elevated screened porch. The lower level has recently been finished with a 5th bedroom/office, a huge family room, bath and tiled floors throughout. The home features all new hardwood floors on the main and second floor. Gourmet kitchen with six burner Wolf stove and integrated appliances including two Bosch wall ovens. Expansive master bedroom and a full bath with a claw foot tub and tiled shower. The second level is plumbed for laundry and has four total bedrooms. Spend time at the Legends playground across the street, at nearby shops or pick apples at Aamodt's Apple Farm on Manning Ave.
Recently sold: $160,000.

Recently sold: $535,000. A comfortably exquisite home located in the conservation-friendly community of Pinecroft. Let your inner chef be inspired by the updated kitchen with beautiful enameled cabinetry, unique granite countertops, rich maple flooring, and informal dining space. The living room boasts the show-stopping striking new fireplace with stone surround, white enameled built-ins, and ship-lap detail. Relish the privacy of the outdoor spaces under the wonderful canopy of White Birch while entertaining on the deck of roasting marshmallows around the new fire pit and treat your senses to the lush and new landscaping. Custom maple kitchen cabinets, high end appliances, beautiful hardwood floors, vaulted ceilings, skylights and open floor plan create a bright, yet warm and inviting home. The walkout lower level is ideal for entertaining complete with custom bar, gas fireplace and full bath. The heated, two car attached garage offers additional storage space. New roof and gutters October 2017, new premium siding completed in April 2019 - this home is ready for you to relax and enjoy!

description: Recently sold: $255,000. Lovingly maintained and owned by the same family for 92 years!! description:
Recently sold: $590,000. See: Austin Jenks House, Wikipedia
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Captain_Austin_Jenks_House

Neighborhood Description

The South Hill is the most desirable neighborhood in historic Stillwater.  This home is located one block from the Old Courthouse where Minnesota became a state.  It is one block from the Saturday Farmer's Market, one block from St. Michael's Catholic Church, and across the street from St. Mary's Catholic Church and St. Paul's Lutheran Church.  Main Street Stillwater is three blocks east and down the city steps.  The home and neighborhood have many beautiful views of Stillwater, the National Wild and Scenic St. Croix River, and many other nicely restored Victorian era houses.   The neighborhood is clean, friendly, and safe, with easy walks to town, church and school.  This is a marvelous place to raise a family, to host and entertain guests, or to enjoy a peaceful retirement.

description:
Recently sold: $502,000. This warm and inviting home sits on a lush 2.59 acre plat of land. There is plenty of privacy to be had with the abundant, mature trees. On the North side of the lot there is a large open space to use as you please!
As you enter the home you are greeted by a soaring 2-story entryway and formal living room. As you walk deeper into the home you find yourself in the large kitchen with custom cherry cabinets with abundant storage. From the kitchen you have quick access to either the formal dining room, the deck or the family room with wood-burning fireplace. From the family room or the deck you can access the gorgeous screened porch. Upstairs you will find 4 large bedrooms all with walk-in closets. The master bedroom has a soaring vaulted ceiling and his and her walk in closets. The lower level features a family room, game room, wet bar and a home office! This home is freshly painted, has new carpeting, new furnace and AC and so much more!!

description: Recently sold: $278,000.

Recently sold: $765,000. The James N Castle house was built in 1872 for then US Senator James Castle. The house is a Stick-Style Victorian home, popularized by politicians in Washington DC at the time. Completely historically renovated by the current owners, the Castle House now has 4 bedrooms and 3 1/2 baths including the third floor master suite which is over 800 sq/ft and includes a private bath. Completely new major mechanical systems (HVAC, Pluming and Electrical) among with exterior upgrades and a new roof were completed in 2017. One of the most recognizable and unique homes in Stillwater, the James N Castle house has also been featured in many online blogs and national publications.

description: Recently sold: $945,000. Built by JP Bush Homes with high-end finishes and exceptional quality, this timeless gem is situated on the 18th hole of StoneRidge Golf Club and offers spectacular views of the St Croix Valley.  Enjoy the convenience of main level living with a most efficient, functional floor plan, while generous room sizes make entertaining and everyday living a breeze.  The entire home has a bright and airy feel with its high ceilings and arched entryways, along with oversized windows to allow natural daylight throughout.  The great room itself showcases wall-to-wall, floor-to-ceiling windows for optimal, panoramic views that continue into the gourmet kitchen, presenting marble countertops, white cabinetry, comfortable walnut flooring and a custom ceiling treatment above the informal dining space.  And in the vaulted four-season sunroom, you can relax with your morning coffee and soak in the peace and serenity that surrounds you.  Also featured on the main level is an elegant formal dining room and a stately den that?s encased in wood paneled walls and a coffered ceiling, which also shares a gorgeous double-sided fireplace with the great room.  Lastly, the master suite is a haven, boasting wall-to-wall windows and a vaulted ceiling, as well as a beautiful fireplace and luxurious en suite with marble countertops, whirlpool tub and large walk-in shower with travertine tile.  And its huge walk-in closet is a dream with its extensive organization system and private access to the laundry room.  Three additional bedrooms with walk-in closets can be found in the lower level, along with a full Jack & Jill and 3/4 en suite, walk-thru bath, perfect for guests and family.  In addition, a cozy family room with a stone surround fireplace sits next to the full wet bar, shining with granite countertops, white cabinetry with undermount/display lighting, and a reclaimed wood door to the lovely wine cellar.  The walkout then leads to an extraordinary patio that was specifically designed for fun and entertainment with conversation and dining space, a fire pit, hot tub and even dance floor.  This exquisite property offers unbeatable views and privacy, while still feeling connected to a fabulous neighborhood.  It?s everything a homeowner could ask for.
Recently sold: $250,000.

Beautiful home located in Grant. This home is situated on 3.81 acres (2 Lots), has 3 bedrooms upstairs with two full baths. On the main floor you will find the kitchen, dinning room, sunken living room that has a wood-burning fireplace.  Located through the French doors off the living room you will find the sitting room. The basement has a bedroom and ¾ bath. You will also enjoy the wet bar and generous sized room. New dishwasher (Bosch), New washer/dryer (LG) located upstairs, new water softener and garage doors. 

This home has two lots, so you can sell one if you wish. Biking distance to Mahtomedi Schools. Close to Highway 36 & 694. White Bear Lake is about 5 blocks away, so you can take a dip when you want. Both White Bear Lake and Stillwater are minutes away. You get the best of both worlds with this property.
